 The results of these measurements are shown in Figures 4 and 5.
 We model the observed curve in terms of a quintic polynomial with equation
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
f(\theta_{i},\,a,\,b,\,c,\,d,\,e,\,f)=a\theta_{i}^{5}+b\theta_{i}^{4}+c\theta_{i}^{3}+d\theta_{i}^{2}+e\theta_{i}+f
